Albert7df\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EFixing words\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Albert7df","CreatedById":171609,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-11-14T04:30:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224198568\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022210599\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221668396272\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022156657\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022HebaruSan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, HebaruSan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t know of any way, but maybe someone will stop by and enlighten both of us.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think i have an idea, at least to reduce the reload of the game, if you don\u0027t create any new behaviour or dependency with core, it could work, just create 2 assemblies, one with the dependencies to the core, it could have all Modules and inheritance, and other asembly for the logic, the first one would be almost with the dependency and just call the logic where the real code is, also it inject the real core object to the second assembly. Also play a button that when i click on it, the dll is reloaded with new code, all Modules would readapt to this new logic, at the end, when the pluging would be for production, the first assembly could be throw, and the second assembly just would need to inherith from the right object.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you think it could work?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-11-14T04:34:55Z\u0022 title=\u002211/14/2022 04:34  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 14, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by Albert7df\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Eexplain better.\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-13T03:13:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224198584\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022210599\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221668400213\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022171609\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Albert7df\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/13/2022 at 11:30 PM, Albert7df said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think i have an idea, at least to reduce the reload of the game, if you don\u0027t create any new behaviour or dependency with core, it could work, just create 2 assemblies, one with the dependencies to the core, it could have all Modules and inheritance, and other asembly for the logic, the first one would be almost with the dependency and just call the logic where the real code is, also it inject the real core object to the second assembly. Also play a button that when i click on it, the dll is reloaded with new code, all Modules would readapt to this new logic, at the end, when the pluging would be for production, the first assembly could be throw, and the second assembly just would need to inherith from the right object.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you think it could work?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnly thing you can safely do is to delete all the parts except for one, and don\u0027t have any of the DLCs installed\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pmborg","CreatedById":198861,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-13T12:34:36Z","Content":"